<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 31 at 3:52PM MDT until May 31 at 4:30PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 430 PM MDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN WELD AND NORTHEASTERN BOULDER COUNTIES...
At 350 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Frederick, or
23 miles southwest of Greeley, moving northwest at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.
SOURCE...Trained spotters reported quarter inch hail near Firestone.
IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Longmont, Firestone, Johnstown, Frederick, Milliken, Berthoud, Mead
and Platteville.
HAIL THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.25 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;50 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
